That's a raccoon
tail, Marion.

14:10.630 --> 14:12.130
Oh.
FONZIE:
Hey, no, no, no.

14:12.130 --> 14:13.720
It's off my bike, you know;
it's brought me, like,

14:13.720 --> 14:15.440
years and years
of good luck.

14:15.440 --> 14:17.310
What about your motorcycle jump?

14:17.310 --> 14:20.280
All right, shortcake, that is
the one time I did not have it.

14:22.310 --> 14:24.230
(motorcycle engine revving)

14:39.460 --> 14:42.410
(cheering)

14:42.410 --> 14:44.330
(tires screeching)

14:44.330 --> 14:46.140
(screaming)

14:46.140 --> 14:47.890
Am I dead?

14:50.970 --> 14:52.560
All right, all right,
all right, all right.

14:52.560 --> 14:55.180
But I was up and moving
around in no time. Whoa.

14:55.180 --> 14:57.760
That was a rotten plan, huh?

14:57.760 --> 14:59.180
Your trick didn't work.

14:59.180 --> 15:00.770
Yeah, I know, I know.

15:00.770 --> 15:02.650
You'll walk, uh, whenever.

15:02.650 --> 15:03.990
All right, hold it.

15:03.990 --> 15:07.070
Just don't tell anybody
you saw this.

15:07.570 --> 15:08.570
Saw what?

15:08.570 --> 15:10.580
Now it's whenever.

15:19.080 --> 15:21.590
(groans):
Oh.

15:21.590 --> 15:23.590
(screams):
Ooh!

15:23.590 --> 15:24.590
Fonz, you-you're
standing up!

15:24.590 --> 15:26.090
Of course I'm standing up!

15:26.090 --> 15:28.590
What do you think I'm gonna do,
stay on a couch all my life?

15:29.090 --> 15:31.600
(screams):
Oh!

15:31.600 --> 15:34.100
You-you're walking
real good there, Fonz.

15:34.100 --> 15:35.100
Does your knee hurt?

15:35.100 --> 15:38.100
Of course it hurts; I
just had an operation!

15:38.100 --> 15:39.100
Now, listen to me.

15:39.100 --> 15:40.110
I want to tell
you something.

15:40.110 --> 15:42.610
I'm not doing this
because of your dumb plan.

15:42.610 --> 15:44.610
I just wanted to stretch
my legs, that's all.

15:44.610 --> 15:45.610
Yeah, right, Fonz, right.

15:45.610 --> 15:48.110
(groans):
Oh.

15:48.110 --> 15:51.120
All right, now I'm gonna try to
get my cool into shape here.

16:06.130 --> 16:07.880
How'd I do?
You did great, Fonz.

16:07.880 --> 16:09.470
My face, how's my face?

16:09.970 --> 16:10.970
You-You look cool.

16:11.470 --> 16:12.470
Yeah.
Yeah.

16:12.470 --> 16:13.470
I want to tell you something.

16:13.470 --> 16:14.970
It's killing me,
and no one will never know.

16:14.970 --> 16:16.480
Yeah.

16:17.930 --> 16:19.900
Hey, girls, I'm up!

16:21.900 --> 16:24.980
All right, all right,
I admit that the jump

16:24.980 --> 16:27.900
was not one of the smartest
things I ever did in my life,

16:27.900 --> 16:30.490
but I gave my word and a lot
of people were counting on me.

16:30.490 --> 16:31.990
I have never
walked away from

16:31.990 --> 16:34.530
responsibility
in my life, Jack. Whoa.

16:34.530 --> 16:35.910
This girl could shake you up.

16:35.910 --> 16:37.000
I usually
shake them up.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.000
Don't I, Malph?
I usually shake them up.

16:39.000 --> 16:41.000
Little ball,
stay up there.
Did he come in yet?

16:44.000 --> 16:45.500
Excuse me.

16:45.500 --> 16:47.340
Hi, I'm Louisa.

16:51.540 --> 16:53.050
(high-pitched):
Hi. I'm Potsie Weber.

16:57.050 --> 17:00.140
(laughter)

17:00.140 --> 17:02.550
Oh, I'm feeling so good,
let's sing.

17:02.550 --> 17:03.940
HOWARD:
Yeah.
How about my
theme song?

17:05.940 --> 17:09.480
♪ I found my thrill ♪

17:09.480 --> 17:12.280
♪ I found my thrill... ♪

17:14.230 --> 17:18.540
♪ On Blue-Blue-Blueberry Hill. ♪

17:18.540 --> 17:20.660
(laughter)

17:20.660 --> 17:22.240
Yeah, that was
a good one.

17:22.240 --> 17:23.290
(door buzzer sounds)

17:23.290 --> 17:24.880
Ah.

17:24.880 --> 17:26.380
Marion, I got
a big surprise for you.

17:26.380 --> 17:27.380
MARION:
What?

17:27.380 --> 17:29.380
The lady who introduced us.

17:29.380 --> 17:30.330
Your cousin Nancy?

17:30.330 --> 17:31.920
Howie!

17:31.920 --> 17:33.920
Oh!

17:33.920 --> 17:35.420
How are you?

17:35.420 --> 17:37.810
I haven't seen you
in so many years!

17:37.810 --> 17:39.510
(women chattering, door closes)

17:39.510 --> 17:41.090
Hey, where are the kids?

17:41.090 --> 17:43.510
Ah, you must be...

17:43.510 --> 17:45.600
Hey.
Richie!

17:45.600 --> 17:46.600
Whoa.
(chuckles)

17:46.600 --> 17:48.600
HOWARD:
Uh, no, no.

17:48.600 --> 17:50.190
No, Nancy,
that's not...

17:50.190 --> 17:53.160
Nancy, this is
our little Richie.

17:53.160 --> 17:54.740
Oh, cute!

17:54.740 --> 17:55.520
So clean-cut.

17:57.610 --> 18:00.160
And you,

18:00.160 --> 18:03.750
you must be
little Joanie, big Joanie.

18:04.250 --> 18:07.750
Oh, you have a lot of troubles
coming your way.

18:07.750 --> 18:09.250
Everyone, I'd
like you to meet

18:09.250 --> 18:11.260
my favorite cousin,
Nancy Blansky.

18:11.260 --> 18:13.260
Hi. How are you?
Hi.
Nice seeing you.

18:13.260 --> 18:14.430
Hey, Howie,

18:14.430 --> 18:16.510
you've put on a couple,
haven't you?

18:16.510 --> 18:18.010
Used to be my
favorite cousin.

18:18.010 --> 18:19.010
(chuckles)

18:19.010 --> 18:22.020
Did you come from Las Vegas
just for our anniversary?

18:22.020 --> 18:25.020
No, sweetheart,
I was in Cicero catching an act,

18:25.020 --> 18:26.520
and I was so close by,
I thought I'd come over.

18:26.520 --> 18:29.020
Oh.
Nancy's in charge
of entertainment

18:29.020 --> 18:30.310
at the
Oasis Hotel.

18:30.310 --> 18:31.390
Oh, yeah?
Well, if you're

18:31.390 --> 18:33.400
in the market for talent,
look no further.

18:33.400 --> 18:34.780
Yeah.

18:34.780 --> 18:38.450
♪ Hey, Venus ♪

18:38.450 --> 18:41.150
♪ Oh, Venus ♪

18:41.150 --> 18:43.070
♪ Make my wish come true ♪

18:44.370 --> 18:47.960
♪ Make my wish come true ♪

18:47.960 --> 18:50.250
♪ Make my wish
come true. ♪

18:50.250 --> 18:52.830
♪ Dearly, I held you ♪

18:52.830 --> 18:55.330
♪ Close in my arms ♪

18:55.330 --> 18:57.840
♪ Angels were singing ♪

18:57.840 --> 19:00.140
♪ A hymn to your charms. ♪

19:04.430 --> 19:06.430
♪ Looks like the sun to me,
well, it's late ♪

19:11.520 --> 19:13.100
(tango music playing)

19:22.280 --> 19:25.160
(Russian folk music playing)

19:52.020 --> 19:55.140
(jazz music playing)

19:55.140 --> 19:57.530
(scatting)

20:01.400 --> 20:02.900
You didn't say anything
about my growing.

20:11.660 --> 20:15.750
BOTH:
♪ We could raise a family ♪

20:15.750 --> 20:17.970
♪ A boy for you ♪

20:17.970 --> 20:20.050
♪ A girl for me ♪

20:20.050 --> 20:22.050
♪ Can't you see ♪

20:22.050 --> 20:23.970
♪ How happy we could be? ♪

20:27.930 --> 20:29.930
(music stops)

20:33.430 --> 20:35.430
(all chattering, laughter)

20:35.430 --> 20:37.940
Hey, hey, Marion.

20:37.940 --> 20:39.940
I haven't even
given you my present.

20:39.940 --> 20:41.940
Oh, thank
you, Howard.

20:41.940 --> 20:43.440
Hey, what'd you
get her, Mr. C.?

20:43.440 --> 20:44.940
Three balloons.

20:44.940 --> 20:47.530
Crackerjack?!

20:47.530 --> 20:48.530
Well, look inside.

20:48.530 --> 20:50.530
(candy rattling)

20:51.500 --> 20:53.090
Oh.

20:53.090 --> 20:54.590
It's a toy
engagement ring.

20:54.590 --> 20:55.590
That is not
funny, Howard.

20:55.590 --> 20:57.340
POTSIE:
Oh, that isn't funny.
You know I...

20:57.340 --> 20:58.420
It's a real one, Marion!

20:58.420 --> 20:59.420
Let me see it.

20:59.420 --> 21:02.430
I've always wanted to have
a real engagement ring.

21:02.430 --> 21:04.930
Here, let me take a look;
I know about these things.

21:04.930 --> 21:06.720
I've been around
enough showgirls.

21:06.720 --> 21:08.550
Well...

21:08.550 --> 21:11.050
I'm sorry to tell you, Marion,
that's the real thing.

21:12.520 --> 21:14.520
(screams)

21:14.520 --> 21:16.310
Oh, How... Oh!

21:16.310 --> 21:19.390
(laughing)

21:19.390 --> 21:20.900
Thank you!

21:20.900 --> 21:22.280
Oh.

21:22.280 --> 21:23.870
HOWARD:
Ah, look at this.

21:23.870 --> 21:25.370
(all aahing, chattering)

21:25.370 --> 21:27.870
♪ For they're
a jolly good couple ♪

21:27.870 --> 21:30.370
♪ For they're a jolly
good couple ♪

21:30.370 --> 21:33.880
♪ For they're
a jolly good couple ♪

21:33.880 --> 21:36.880
♪ On their 20th anniversary ♪
♪ Which nobody can deny. ♪

21:36.880 --> 21:38.880
(cheering)

21:38.880 --> 21:41.380
♪ La, la, la-la, la,
la, la, la ♪

21:41.880 --> 21:42.880
♪ La-la, la-la la-la, la. ♪

21:48.810 --> 21:50.890
(all chattering)
Bye-bye, nice meeting you.

21:50.890 --> 21:51.890
(phone ringing)

21:51.890 --> 21:53.400
Phone, Mom.
(chuckles)

21:53.400 --> 21:54.900
Hey, listen, I think
I'd better be going.
Hello.

21:54.900 --> 21:56.900
I have to get to Vegas.
Yes, just
a minute.

21:56.900 --> 21:58.480
Arthur.
What?

21:58.480 --> 22:00.490
This is someone called
the Aloha Pussycats.

22:00.490 --> 22:01.990
Mm-hmm?
In between giggling,

22:01.990 --> 22:03.990
it seems that you are
20 minutes late.

22:03.990 --> 22:05.490
Well, tell them
to relax, man.

22:05.490 --> 22:06.990
It'll be worth it,
right? Hey.

22:06.990 --> 22:08.490
He's on his way.

22:08.490 --> 22:10.580
The Aloha
Pussycats?

22:10.580 --> 22:12.410
You'd, uh, do very
well in Vegas.

22:12.410 --> 22:14.500
Well, thank you very much,
but I got to tell you something.

22:14.500 --> 22:16.340
I do very well everywhere!

22:19.040 --> 22:20.120
Hey, listen,
congrats, huh?

22:20.120 --> 22:22.120
Really, Mrs. C.
Oh, thank you.

22:22.120 --> 22:23.960
Nancy Blansky, huh?

22:23.960 --> 22:25.040
Knock
yourself out.

22:25.040 --> 22:26.550
All right, hey!
I'll see you.

22:26.550 --> 22:27.550
Thanks, Fonz.
Bye, Fonz.

22:27.550 --> 22:29.050
Good-bye.
Oh!

22:29.050 --> 22:31.050
Listen, babies,
I got to go,

22:31.050 --> 22:33.050
but next time
I'm in the neighborhood,

22:33.050 --> 22:34.190
I'll drop in, okay?
Yeah.

22:34.190 --> 22:35.770
Don't wait till
our 40th anniversary.

22:35.770 --> 22:37.310
Uh, so long, kids.

22:37.310 --> 22:39.020
Bye.
So long.

22:39.020 --> 22:40.110
Howie.
Hmm?

22:40.110 --> 22:42.110
One more time.

22:48.400 --> 22:51.900
Oh, Howard, thank you
for that anniversary.

22:51.900 --> 22:53.710
Mm-hmm.

22:53.710 --> 22:55.790
I think they want
to be alone.

22:55.790 --> 22:56.790
Yep.

22:56.790 --> 22:58.290
They're at it again.

22:58.290 --> 23:01.300
We've got the
friskiest parents.

23:01.300 --> 23:03.300
What's your project,
Joanie?

23:03.300 --> 23:04.580
Oh, I wrote a
composition:

23:04.580 --> 23:07.000
"My Parents Are Still Frisky."

23:09.390 --> 23:11.390
Well, what do you
want to do?

23:15.390 --> 23:16.900
Are you getting frisky?

23:16.900 --> 23:18.900
(both laugh)

23:18.900 --> 23:21.400
It's only Thursday!

23:23.400 --> 23:24.570
Oh, boy.

23:24.570 --> 23:27.440
Every Saturday,
it's the same thing.

23:34.580 --> 23:37.580
Come on, sweetheart,
let's go to sleep.

23:37.580 --> 23:39.580
I should clean up.

23:39.580 --> 23:42.090
Oh, it can wait
till tomorrow.

23:42.090 --> 23:44.090
You know, we were
doing the same thing

23:44.090 --> 23:46.210
20 years ago tonight.

23:46.210 --> 23:48.290
Mmm.

23:48.290 --> 23:49.800
Only then, we were running.

23:49.800 --> 23:51.880
(sighs)

23:53.880 --> 23:56.300
♪ These happy days
are yours and mine ♪

23:56.300 --> 23:57.390
♪ These are such happy days. ♪

24:04.060 --> 24:06.560
♪ Good-bye, gray sky,
hello, blue ♪

24:06.560 --> 24:08.980
♪ There's nothing can hold me
when I hold you ♪

24:08.980 --> 24:11.400
♪ It feels so right,
it can't be wrong ♪

24:11.400 --> 24:14.070
♪ Rockin' and rollin'
all week long ♪

